shared_text:
Each Mind Matters
September 2 at 5:11 PM ¬∑

Is someone you care about not acting like themselves? If you‚Äôre worried about someone, the best thing that you can do is to trust your instincts and speak up! Mention the behaviors you have been noticing and ask directly about suicide. Saying the words directly, ‚ÄúAre you thinking about suicide?‚Äù can be difficult to say, but when it comes to suicide prevention, none are more important.
And remember you are not alone. Call the National Suicide Prevention Lifeline '1-800-273-TALK (8255)' if you are concerned about a loved one or in crisis yourself.
To learn more about the warning signs for suicide and tips to prepare for a conversation with someone you are concerned about visit suicideispreventable.org.

post_text:
Dear senior students,

We will host a senior celebratory drive-thru on Thursday, May 21st in your honor. The idea is to recognize you and all of your achievements. During this event, you will receive your cap and gown, graduation cords, and scholarships. The event will be live streamed for family members to celebrate with you virtually. During this event, you will have the opportunity to return books, Chromebooks (if you don't need them) and pay any outstanding fees you may have. Please refer to the attached document for details on this event.

We hope you can join us on this special day designed just for you.
text:
Dear senior students,

We will host a senior celebratory drive-thru on Thursday, May 21st in your honor. The idea is to recognize you and all of your achievements. During this event, you will receive your cap and gown, graduation cords, and scholarships. The event will be live streamed for family members to celebrate with you virtually. During this event, you will have the opportunity to return books, Chromebooks (if you don't need them) and pay any outstanding fees you may have. Please refer to the attached document for details on this event.

We hope you can join us on this special day designed just for you.

Happy Teacher‚Äôs Day/ Staff Appreciation Day

I want to let the Le Grand High School Staff know how amazing you are. Our teachers play a pivotal role in the students‚Äô lives. This pandemic has made me appreciate even more how teachers have adapted their curriculum for digital learning, how the food service workers have made sure the students are fed, how the custodians are working to clean our facilities, how our Office Staff is working by our sides to keep things running and messages out to parents, our After School Staff and Counselors who check in with our families and most of all our Technology Staff who‚Äôs making sure our students and staff stay connected. You make Le Grand High School District an AMAZING place.

#sendTeacherandStaffLove
